---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = 'Cibolo & Schertz Neighborhoods | Cody Posey';
const pageDescription = 'Explore the top neighborhoods in Cibolo and Schertz, TX — from Saddle Creek Ranch and Cibolo Valley Ranch to master-planned communities and new construction.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/cibolo-schertz/neighborhoods' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Cibolo & Schertz', url: '/cibolo-schertz' },
    { name: 'Neighborhoods', url: '/cibolo-schertz/neighborhoods' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="cs-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/cibolo-schertz/">Cibolo / Schertz</a> <span>/</span> <span>Neighborhoods</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Cibolo / Schertz <span style="color:#FF1616;">Neighborhoods</span></h1>
        <p>Find the community that fits your family and lifestyle</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="cs-page-intro cs-page-intro--centered">The Cibolo/Schertz area offers a variety of well-established and newer neighborhoods, all served by the highly rated SCUCISD school district. Whether you are looking for a starter home or an executive property, there is a community here for you.</p>
        <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 1.5rem auto 0; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.8; text-align: center;">Cibolo and Schertz sit along the I-35 corridor northeast of San Antonio, offering suburban convenience with easy access to Randolph Air Force Base, Fort Sam Houston, and the San Antonio job market. These sister cities have experienced rapid growth over the past decade thanks to top-rated schools, well-planned master communities, and home prices that remain competitive compared to central San Antonio. The area is popular with military families, young professionals, and growing households who want modern construction, strong neighborhood amenities, and a family-oriented atmosphere. Most neighborhoods here feature sidewalk-lined streets, community parks, and pools — along with quick access to retail and dining along FM 1103 and FM 78.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Neighborhoods -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Top <span class="accent">Neighborhoods</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-hood">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cs-saddle-creek.png" alt="Saddle Creek Ranch homes" class="cs-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="cs-hood__header">
            <h3>Saddle Creek Ranch</h3>
            <span class="cs-hood__price">$300K - $450K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Saddle Creek Ranch is a welcoming community offering a peaceful suburban lifestyle in the heart of the Cibolo/Schertz area. Residents enjoy family-friendly amenities including a community pool, clubhouse, playgrounds, sports courts, picnic areas, and walking and jogging trails. Homes feature modern open-concept layouts with stylish interiors, and the neighborhood is served by SCUCISD schools. The community includes a mix of one and two-story homes from builders known for quality construction and energy efficiency. Lot sizes are generous compared to comparable neighborhoods closer to San Antonio, and many homes include three-car garages, covered patios, and upgraded kitchen packages. Saddle Creek Ranch is especially popular with families relocating from San Antonio who want more space without a long commute.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-hood">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cs-falcon-ridge.png" alt="Falcon Ridge homes" class="cs-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="cs-hood__header">
            <h3>Falcon Ridge</h3>
            <span class="cs-hood__price">$280K - $400K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Falcon Ridge is an established, family-oriented community known for its mature landscaping and strong neighborhood identity. Amenities include a community park, playground, BBQ grills, a large outdoor pool with lap lanes, clubhouse, pickleball and tennis courts, and sand volleyball. Homes come in one and two-story options with spacious backyards, and the neighborhood is served by SCUCISD schools. As one of the more established communities in the area, Falcon Ridge benefits from mature trees and well-maintained common areas that newer neighborhoods have not yet developed. The active HOA organizes seasonal events that foster a genuine sense of community. Home styles range from traditional Texas ranch to transitional designs with stone and stucco exteriors, and many properties have been updated with modern finishes by current owners.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-hood">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cs-bentwood-ranch.png" alt="Bentwood Ranch homes" class="cs-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="cs-hood__header">
            <h3>Bentwood Ranch</h3>
            <span class="cs-hood__price">$280K - $380K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Bentwood Ranch is a sought-after suburban community with a strong neighborhood feel, featuring well-kept streets, mature trees, and beautifully landscaped yards. Residents enjoy a community pool, playground, and walking trails throughout the neighborhood. Homes offer spacious floorplans on ample lots, making it an ideal choice for families within the SCUCISD school district. The neighborhood is conveniently located near shopping, dining, and major employers, with quick access to I-35 and Loop 1604. Homes in Bentwood Ranch typically feature four to five bedrooms with open-concept living areas, granite countertops, and covered back patios. The community appeals to move-up buyers and military families stationed at nearby Randolph AFB who want a stable, well-maintained neighborhood with room to grow.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-hood">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cs-turning-stone.png" alt="Turning Stone homes" class="cs-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="cs-hood__header">
            <h3>Turning Stone</h3>
            <span class="cs-hood__price">$350K - $450K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Turning Stone offers upscale, peaceful suburban living with an impressive array of community amenities including parks, walking trails, green spaces, an onsite elementary school, volleyball, basketball, and tennis courts, a cabana, and a beach entry pool. Homes are well-maintained and spacious with contemporary finishes, and the neighborhood is served by SCUCISD schools. The presence of an onsite elementary school is a major draw for families with young children, eliminating long bus rides and making school drop-off simple. Homes in Turning Stone feature upgraded finishes such as engineered hardwood floors, quartz countertops, and stainless steel appliance packages. The neighborhood maintains a polished appearance through active HOA management and architectural standards that keep the community looking consistent and well cared for.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-hood">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cs-cibolo-valley.png" alt="Cibolo Valley Ranch homes" class="cs-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="cs-hood__header">
            <h3>Cibolo Valley Ranch</h3>
            <span class="cs-hood__price">$250K - $350K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Cibolo Valley Ranch is a well-established master-planned community with a family-oriented atmosphere that appeals to a wide range of buyers. Residents enjoy resort-style pool access, a fitness center, and miles of hiking and biking trails throughout the neighborhood. Homes range from midsize single-family options to larger estates on spacious lots, all within the SCUCISD school district. With homes starting in the $250K range, Cibolo Valley Ranch is one of the most accessible master-planned communities in the area for first-time buyers. The neighborhood has been developed in phases over several years, so buyers can choose between established sections with mature landscaping and newer sections with the latest builder designs. The trails system connects to parks throughout the community, making it easy to stay active without leaving the neighborhood.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- School District -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>School <span class="accent">District</span></h2>
          <p>One of the highest-rated school districts in the San Antonio metro</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-schools__grid">
          <a href="https://www.scuc.txed.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-schools__card">
            <h3>Schertz-Cibolo-Universal City ISD (SCUCISD)</h3>
            <p>An A-rated district known for academic excellence, strong athletics, and community engagement. Steele High School and Byron P. Steele II are among the top-rated campuses. The district serves Schertz, Cibolo, and Universal City.</p>
            <span class="cs-schools__link">Visit SCUCISD Website →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Need Help <span class="accent">Choosing a Neighborhood</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I can walk you through the differences between communities and help you focus your search on neighborhoods that match your priorities.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Get Help Choosing a Neighborhood</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png" />

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Cibolo and Schertz Neighborhoods</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What are the best neighborhoods in Cibolo and Schertz for families?</summary>
          <p>Turning Stone and Saddle Creek Ranch are two of the top choices for families in the Cibolo/Schertz area. Turning Stone stands out for having an onsite elementary school, which makes daily routines much easier for parents with young children. It also offers a full suite of amenities including parks, sports courts, and a beach entry pool. Saddle Creek Ranch is another strong option with playgrounds, walking trails, and modern homes with open-concept layouts. Both communities are served by SCUCISD, one of the highest-rated school districts in the San Antonio metro.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the average home price in Cibolo and Schertz?</summary>
          <p>Home prices in the Cibolo/Schertz area typically range from the mid $200Ks to the mid $400Ks, depending on the neighborhood, home size, and age of construction. Cibolo Valley Ranch offers some of the most affordable options starting around $250K, while Turning Stone and Saddle Creek Ranch trend higher in the $300K to $450K range for newer or larger homes. Compared to similar communities in central San Antonio or New Braunfels, the Cibolo/Schertz area generally provides more square footage and lot size for the price.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do all Cibolo and Schertz neighborhoods have HOAs?</summary>
          <p>Yes, all five of the major neighborhoods highlighted here — Saddle Creek Ranch, Falcon Ridge, Bentwood Ranch, Turning Stone, and Cibolo Valley Ranch — have active homeowners associations. HOA fees typically range from $30 to $70 per month and cover maintenance of common areas, pools, parks, and trails. The HOAs also enforce architectural and landscaping standards to maintain property values and neighborhood appearance. If you prefer a property without HOA restrictions, there are individual lots and older subdivisions outside of master-planned communities in the broader Cibolo/Schertz area.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best neighborhoods in Cibolo and Schertz for families?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Turning Stone and Saddle Creek Ranch are two of the top choices for families in the Cibolo/Schertz area. Turning Stone stands out for having an onsite elementary school, which makes daily routines much easier for parents with young children. Saddle Creek Ranch is another strong option with playgrounds, walking trails, and modern homes with open-concept layouts. Both communities are served by SCUCISD, one of the highest-rated school districts in the San Antonio metro."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the average home price in Cibolo and Schertz?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Home prices in the Cibolo/Schertz area typically range from the mid $200Ks to the mid $400Ks, depending on the neighborhood, home size, and age of construction. Cibolo Valley Ranch offers some of the most affordable options starting around $250K, while Turning Stone and Saddle Creek Ranch trend higher in the $300K to $450K range."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do all Cibolo and Schertz neighborhoods have HOAs?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, all five of the major neighborhoods highlighted here have active homeowners associations. HOA fees typically range from $30 to $70 per month and cover maintenance of common areas, pools, parks, and trails. If you prefer a property without HOA restrictions, there are individual lots and older subdivisions outside of master-planned communities in the broader Cibolo/Schertz area."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ContactForm context="I need help choosing a neighborhood in Cibolo/Schertz..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .cs-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .cs-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .cs-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .cs-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .cs-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Neighborhood Cards */
  .cs-hood {
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .cs-hood__img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .cs-hood__header {
    padding: 2rem 2rem 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cs-hood__header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cs-hood__price {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #FF1616;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .cs-hood p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding: 0 2rem 2rem;
  }

  /* Schools */
  .cs-schools__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cs-schools__card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cs-schools__card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .cs-schools__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #000;
  }

  .cs-schools__card:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .cs-schools__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cs-schools__link {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cs-hood__header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
